# {{ product_name }} — First sales checklist

This checklist is for the first manual sales attempts. Do not build a client portal before this workflow has been tested with real prospects.

## Before outreach

- [ ] Generate fresh demo reports: `python -m app.demo_reports generate`
- [ ] Open `sales_pack/demo_reports/good_site_demo.html`
- [ ] Open `sales_pack/demo_reports/medium_site_demo.html`
- [ ] Open `sales_pack/demo_reports/problem_site_demo.html`
- [ ] Confirm each demo has `Executive summary`, `Site Health Score`, `Top 3 actions`, owner, next step, and business impact
- [ ] Open the latest `landing_page.html`
- [ ] Confirm the offer reads as a recurring white-label reporting service, not software access

## Who to contact first

Prioritize prospects who already manage client sites:

- SEO freelancers with 3+ client websites
- Small web studios maintaining client websites after launch
- Marketers responsible for several websites

Avoid prospects who only need a one-time deep audit, keyword research, or analytics consulting.

## First contact flow

1. Send a short message from `outreach_messages.md`.
2. Offer a sample report, not a product demo call.
3. If they reply, send one relevant demo report or create a prospect-specific sample.
4. Ask whether this would save them weekly reporting time or help client communication.
5. If yes, send the appropriate plan link or setup form.

## Qualification questions

- How many client sites do you maintain every month?
- Do you currently send weekly or monthly site status updates?
- Who prepares those reports now?
- Would a white-label HTML/PDF report be enough, or do you need manual commentary added?
- Which sites should be included in the first weekly run?

## When to mark the service as validated

The service has early validation when at least one of these happens:

- 3 prospects ask for a sample report;
- 1 prospect agrees to a paid trial;
- 1 agency says the report can be forwarded to their client with minimal editing.

If none of this happens after 20 targeted contacts, improve the report/offer before building more SaaS features.

